modules.description: Provides functions for sampling and analyzing program execution, including start and stop sampling, retrieving sample data, and converting it to human-readable formats. Operates on raw memory buffers and structured data representing performance metrics. Used to profile CPU usage and identify performance bottlenecks in real-time applications.

Provides functions to monitor and control memory allocation behavior, including releasing unused memory, adjusting release rates, and querying numeric properties of the memory allocator. Works with numeric values, strings, and heap profiling data to track memory usage and performance. Used to optimize memory consumption in applications by dynamically adjusting allocation strategies and generating detailed memory usage reports.
